Yelp: Data Mining Final Project¶

EDA - Reviews¶

Project Scope:¶

By utilizing the yelp datasets, we plan to accomplish several tasks:

  • Predict the success of a business in its industry based on the first 5-10 reviews.
  • Predict the success of store expansions based on reviews, should they expand to different locations.

# Function for all necessary text preprocessing steps

def preprocess_text(text):
    # Text Lowercasing
    text = text.lower()
    # Removing Punctuation
    text = text.translate(str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation))
    # Tokenization
    tokens = word_tokenize(text)
    # Removing Stopwords
    stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
    filtered_tokens = [word for word in tokens if word not in stop_words]
    # Lemmatization
    lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
    lemmatized_tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in filtered_tokens]
    # Joining the lemmatized tokens back into a string
    return ' '.join(lemmatized_tokens)

Top-Bigrams for each city¶

In [52]:
for city in sorted(merged_df['city'].unique()):
    city_df = merged_df[merged_df['city'] == city]
    lemmatized_tokens = [review.split() for review in city_df['processed_reviews']]
    token_list = list(itertools.chain(*lemmatized_tokens))
    
    bigrams = list(ngrams(token_list, 2))
    
    counts_no = collections.Counter(bigrams)
    
    clean_reviews = pd.DataFrame(counts_no.most_common(20), columns=['bigram', 'count'])
    clean_reviews['bigram'] = clean_reviews['bigram'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x))
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
    clean_reviews.sort_values(by='count').plot.barh(x='bigram', y='count', ax=ax, color="purple")
    ax.set_title(f"Most Frequently Used Bi-grams in {city} Reviews")
    plt.show()

Word clouds for user_stars¶

In [ ]:
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
from collections import Counter
from wordcloud import WordCloud
In [ ]:
for rating in range(1, 6):
    texts = merged_df[merged_df['user_stars'] == rating]['processed_reviews'].apply(lambda x: ''.join(x))
    
    vectorizer = CountVectorizer(ngram_range=(2, 2))
    bag_of_words = vectorizer.fit_transform(texts)
    
    sum_words = bag_of_words.sum(axis=0)
    words_freq = [(word, sum_words[0, idx]) for word, idx in vectorizer.vocabulary_.items()]
    words_freq = sorted(words_freq, key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    words_dict = dict(words_freq)
    
    WC_height = 1000
    WC_width = 1500
    WC_max_words = 200
    wordCloud = WordCloud(max_words=WC_max_words, height=WC_height, width=WC_width)
    wordCloud.generate_from_frequencies(words_dict)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 8))
    plt.imshow(wordCloud, interpolation="bilinear")
    plt.title('Word Cloud for Rating ' + str(rating))
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.show()
